{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-228-a-peek-at-3d-touch"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"3D Touch adds a completely new dimension to the iOS user interface and introduces an entirely new way to interact with your iPhone. Explore the existing API and get introduced to additions in iOS 10 that allow you to push the boundaries of 3D Touch. Learn about best practices for incorporating 3D Touch into your apps, how to add support for Quick Actions, Peek, and Pop.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-228-A-Peek-at-3D-Touch","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/228\/","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex"}},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","title":"A Peek at 3D Touch","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC16"},"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Related Sessions","anchor":"Related-Sessions","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-205-Whats-New-in-Cocoa-Touch","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-216-Advances-in-UIKit-Animations-and-Transitions","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-220-Leveraging-Touch-Input-on-iOS"],"type":"links","style":"list"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"WWDC16.jpeg":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16.jpeg"}],"identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg","alt":null,"type":"image"},"WWDC16-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-Icon.png"}],"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16","abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 8, Swift 3.0, iOS 10, macOS 10.12 (Sierra), tvOS 10, watchOS 3.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg"}],"title":"WWDC16"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"title":"Learn More…","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2016/228/":{"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/228\/","checksum":null,"type":"download","url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/228\/"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-220-Leveraging-Touch-Input-on-iOS":{"role":"sampleCode","title":"Leveraging Touch Input on iOS","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-220-leveraging-touch-input-on-ios","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-220-Leveraging-Touch-Input-on-iOS","abstract":[{"text":"Learn essential best practices for using event input from Apple Pencil in your drawing apps. Gain a practical understanding of the concepts behind efficient and accurate touch event processing. Get details about the touch input pipeline on iOS and how to take advantage of it in all your apps.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-205-Whats-New-in-Cocoa-Touch":{"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-205-Whats-New-in-Cocoa-Touch","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The UIKit framework provides the crucial infrastructure needed to construct and manage iOS apps, and UIKit continues to advance the state of the art for app design with many new features. Dive straight into new features across the iOS frameworks that allow your apps to take advantage of many new system services, as well as to offer services to other apps. This is your first stop to discover the many sessions to see about harnessing the power of iOS 10."}],"title":"What’s New in Cocoa Touch","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-205-whats-new-in-cocoa-touch","type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"role":"collection","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"type":"topic","title":"WWDC Notes","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-216-Advances-in-UIKit-Animations-and-Transitions":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-216-advances-in-uikit-animations-and-transitions","title":"Advances in UIKit Animations and Transitions","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-216-Advances-in-UIKit-Animations-and-Transitions","abstract":[{"text":"Direct onscreen manipulation is the cornerstone of the user experience on iOS. iOS 10 includes new support for making onscreen interactions even more immersive and interactive. Dive straight into the philosophy and techniques of building completely interactive, interruptible animations in your apps.","type":"text"}]}}}